nl.naturalis.nda.elasticsearch.load.brahms

Class BrahmsDumpUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.naturalis.nda.elasticsearch.load.brahms.BrahmsDumpUtil
  • Deprecated. 
    UTF-8 conversion now happends on the fly

    public class BrahmsDumpUtil
extends Object
    Utility class for determining file encoding of Brahms dumps, and for converting them to UTF-8. This class is not used any longer because the conversion is now done on the fly (while importing specimens/multimedia).
    Author:
    Ayco Holleman

      • detectEncoding

        public static void detectEncoding()
                           throws IOException
        Deprecated. 
        Utility method to detect character set in Brahms dumps. Not part of the import work flow. Two different character set detector libraries are used: universalchardet (Mozilla) en ICU (IBM). Mozilla could not detect any character set at all. ICU settled on ISO-8859-1. Nonetheless, we assume the character set in the Brahms dumps is CP-1252, because that seemed to give the best results (least "funny" characters).
        Throws:
        IOException
